<2ND_LINE>PM-Child-Dog,0278</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Neglected Child Ate Off Floor With Dog, Makes Only Dog-Like Sounds</HEAD>
<DATELINE>METTMANN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 4-year-old boy ate food scraps
on the floor with his family's German shepherd for about a year and
can only howl and whine like a dog because of parental neglect,
police said today.
   The mass-circulation Bild newspaper said the female German
shepherd had ``raised'' the child, but authorities said that was an
exaggeration. Bild identified the boy only as Horst.
   ``The child is unable to speak, because his parents never spoke
to him,'' said Mettmann police spokesman Wolfgang Schauer, adding
the boy only makes dog-like sounds.
   ``The dog had become a bigger part of his (the child's) life
than his parents,'' said the police spokesman in Mettmann, eight
miles from Duesseldorf.
   Schauer told The Associated Press in a telephone interview the
boy routinely shared food scraps with the animal on the kitchen
floor of the family's apartment and that the boy did not know how
to eat at the table.
   Authorities did not release the family's name, but said the
parents were being investigated. Bild said the father was a
30-year-old unemployed butcher.
   The couple routinely left the child alone with the dog in the
apartment during the day, Bild reported.
   The child's grandfather came for a visit last week and found the
youngster on the floor sharing a piece of meat with the dog, the
police spokesman said.
   The grandfather immediately notified authorities, and the child
was taken to a children's hospital in nearby Wuppertal, said
Schauer.
   Bild said the child's only word was ``Asta,'' the dog's name.
</TEXT>
