<1ST_LINE>r a PM-EmpireJumper     03-18 0241</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Empire Jumper,0247</2ND_LINE>
<NOTE>Eds: Retransmitting a0543 to make overline conform to story</NOTE>
<HEAD>Man Dies After Jumping From Empire State Building</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man fell to his death early today after he
apparently jumped from the 86th-floor observation deck of the
Empire State Building and landed on a ledge five floors below,
officials said.
   Steven Murkey, 24, was pronounced dead at 12:25 a.m. today in
the emergency room of Bellevue Hospital Center, the hospital's
night supervisor Robert Frazier said.
   Two witnesses at the observatory saw the man jump, but fled
before police could question them, said police Officer Paul Pisano.
   An ambulance crew called to the skyscraper at 11:38 p.m.
Thursday pulled him inside from a window on the 81st floor,
authorities said.
   Emergency Medical Services Capt. Don Rothschild said the man may
have climbed over a fence around the observation deck of the
102-story building, the city's second-talest and a popular tourist
attraction.
   A security guard at the Empire State Building said no one would
be available from there to answer questions until later today.
   There have been more than 30 suicides at the skyscraper, the
world's tallest when it opened in 1931. It since has been
surpassed, first by the World Trade Center in New York, then by the
Sears Tower in Chicago.
   Most of those who have leaped to their deaths never made it to
the street, landing instead on one of the building's setbacks.
</TEXT>
