<1ST_LINE>r a PM-People-Feinstein     03-18 0193</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-People-Feinstein,0198</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Former SF Mayor Named to Bank Board</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former Mayor Dianne Feinstein has been
named to the board of Bancal Tri-State Corp. and its Bank of
California subsidiary.
   ``I'm a private citizen and not looking to make any political
decisions this year,'' she said Thursday after her election to the
board. Feinstein said the job with the San Francisco-based bank is
``an opportunity for me to learn more about a major business in the
Bay area and the state of California.''
   The BanCal holding company, which does business in California,
Oregon and Washington, has approximately $4 billion in assets.
   The board was expanded from 15 to 16 members to make room for
the ex-mayor, who attended her first meeting after her election and
was assigned to the trust committee. Trust operations account for
30 percent of the bank's business.
   ``I'm just a beginner,'' she said later. ``I'm learning.''
   The job pays $10,000 a year plus $500 per board meeting and $400
for each committee meeting, up to a total of $19,000, a bank
spokeswoman said. It marks Feinstein's first professional venture
since leaving office two months ago.
</TEXT>
