<1ST_LINE>r a AM-ChildStalker     03-18 0367</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Child Stalker,0377</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Police Escort School Buses In Search For Child Stalker</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PLAISTOW, N.H. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Parents and schools are keeping closer
watch on their children as authorities and volunteers look for a
man who has tried to lure youngsters into his car in New
Hampshire-Massachusetts border communities.
   Police report that the man has approached children at least a
dozen times in the last three weeks in Atkinson and Plaistow, as
well as over the border in Merrimac, Haverhill and Methuen, Mass.
   Generally, they say, he drives alongside youngsters walking
alone in the late afternoon or early evening, rolls down the window
and asks the children their names and where they are going, then
offers a ride.
   The man has driven slowly by children in his town, shouting,
``I'm going to get you,'' Atkinson Police Chief Phillip Consentino
said.
   So far, police say, he has not been able to lure anyone into his
big brown or maroon car, but he gotten out and chased a couple of
kids, one of whom escaped to home as the man fell on ice.
   ``My concern is that there is going to be one gullible kid out
there that is going to get in a car,'' said Plaistow police Sgt.
Thomas Bourque. ``Then who knows what is going to happen.''
   He said a Plaistow youngster was chased on foot by the man, who
got back into his car and left when the youngster ran to a house
and pounded on the door.
   Police have distributed a composite drawing of the man, and it
is posted in schools and on school buses. Schools are scheduling
programs to teach children how to deal with strangers and to
instruct parents.
   Bus drivers have met to talk about how to better protect their
riders, and Atkinson police have been following buses.
   In Plaistow, police in unmarked cars, people from the schools or
parents have been watching for the stalker.
   Bourque said kids are ``showing some fear,'' but ``seem to know
what to do _ they are running. They don't talk to the guy.''
   The children are fleeing so quickly, that none has been able to
get the license plate number of the man's car.
</TEXT>
