</TEXT>
<DATELINE>COLUMBIA, S.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The coordinator of Jesse Jackson's
presidential campaign in South Carolina says he won't ask a judge
to stop county conventions Monday after party chairmen agreed to
send delegate lists by Saturday.
   ``We are not going to spend time with legal action,'' Kevin Gray
said Friday, one of a growing number of Democrats who believe the
party should be holding a primary in the state.
   Nineteen county conventions are meeting Monday and another 27
counties are meeting March 28. Jackson was the overwhelming winner
at last Saturday's 1,788 precinct caucus meetings.
</TEXT>
