<1ST_LINE>u w BC-NorthText     03-18 0402</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-North Text,380</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a transcript of the announcement
Friday by Lt. Col. Oliver North, who is facing trial in the
Iran-Contra case, on his request to retire from the Marine Corps.
   There have been many inquiries this afternoon regarding a story,
apparently out of the Pentagon, about my status in the Marine Corps.
   And I would like to clarify the situation at this time.
   I love the United States Marine Corps, and the courageous
brothers in arms that I have served with over the past 20 years.
   Since graduating from the United States Naval Academy, my goal
has simply been to serve our country as a Marine for as long as
possible.
   Unfortunately, the indictment delivered two days ago places me
in a situation where my continued service would be inconsistent
with preparing and presenting a vigorous defense against these
unfounded charges.
   My attorney, Brendan Sullivan, has informed me that the defense
against these charges may require him to issue subpoenas for the
testimony and records of the highest-ranking officials of our
government.
   That strikes me as a course of action incompatible with my
continued service as a Marine officer.
   Accordingly, with great sadness, I have tendered my request to
retire from the Marine Corps.
   For over 16 months, I have silently endured a torrent of media
speculation, as the largest investigation in the history of our
country has probed every aspect of my personal and professional
life, and that of my family.
   I have not responded, except when required by law during the
course of the congressional hearings last summer.
   Further silence is a disservice to me, my family, and the brave
people I have served and worked with on matters of great importance
to our country.
   Moreover, while on active duty, I am not fully free to speak out
or to take other actions which may be necessary.
   The months ahead will be difficult, and I recognize that
fighting a prosecutor with an unlimited budget, an enormous staff,
is a formidable and costly task for me and my counsel.
   My family and I continue to take heart from the overwhelming
expressions of love and concern and encouragement by countless
freedom-loving people.
   We are extremely grateful.
   Your prayers and support have helped us to endure this ordeal in
Washington.
   I thank you.
   God bless you.
   Semper fidelis.
   Thank you.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>End North Text _ 1 Take</HEAD>
