<HEAD>Democrats Add Another Delegate, Making Total 4,163</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Democratic Party on Friday added another
delegate to the number attending this summer's national convention
in Atlanta, bringing the total to 4,163.
   Mayor Joseph Riley of Charleston, S.C., will attend as a
representative of the National Conference of Democratic Mayors.
   That seat had been held by Detroit Mayor Coleman A. Young, who
also has claim to a delegate's seat because he is a member of the
Democratic National Committee from Michigan.
   Under party rules, Young could assign another mayor to take his
seat to represent the mayors' conference, according to Jim Carey,
executive director of the party's Compliance Assistance Commission.
