sparing the country a period of prolonged political upheaval,
including widespread suffering.
   The country has been virtually paralyzed economically for most
of the past two weeks.
   The government of Spain has said it would be wiling to admit
Noriega provided he requests political asylum and the United States
agrees not to seek his extradition.
