<HEAD>Security Council To Meet Urgently Over Nicaragua-Honduras Crisis</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Honduras, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>UNITED NATIONS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Security Council will meet in urgent
session Friday on the Nicaraguan-Honduran border crisis and on the
dispatch of U.S. troops to Honduras.
   Nicaragua sought the meeting at President Daniel Ortega's
request, diplomats said. Envoys of the United States, Nicaragua and
