<HEAD>Firestone To Merge with Bridgestone</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Firestone Tire & Rubber Co. announced Thursday it
has agreed to a $2.6 billion takeover by No. 1 tire-maker
Bridgestone Corp.
   Firestone's board unanimously recommended shareholders accept an
offer of $80 a share from Tokyo-based Bridgestone for all
outstanding common shares.
   Firestone also said its board recommended that shareholders
reject a rival, unsolicited $58-a-share buyout offer from Italian
tiremaker Pirelli SpA.
   The Bridgestone offer is subject to at least two-thirds of the
shares being tendered and approval of the deal by Firestone
shareholders.
   The agreement was announced after the stock market closed.
Firestone stock dipped 62{ cents to $62.50 a share Thursday on the
New York Stock Exchange.
   Firestone ranks fourth in tire sales worldwide, behind Goodyear,
Michelin and Bridgestone, according to industry estimates.
</TEXT>
