<HEAD>Plane Crashes into Playground</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: UPDATES throughout with details of plane, officials
confirming no schoolchildren were hurt.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>BAKERSFIELD, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A single-engine plane crashed in a
schoolyard Thursday, but the pilot was the only one injured,
authorities said.
   ``Nobody was out in the playground at the time,'' said Wilbur
Friend, air traffic manager for the Federal Aviation Administration
tower at Meadows Field. The pilot's name and the extent of his
injuries were unavailable.
   Friend said the pilot was making his final approach to Meadows
Field, Bakersfield's main commercial airport, when his engine lost
power. He attempted an emergency landing.
   The plane crashed about a mile short of Meadows Field at the
North Beardsley School, which consists of kindergarten through
third grade. No fire was reported.
   The National Transportation Safety Board will investigate.
</TEXT>
